                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2635: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-15T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. No objection is perceived to the suggestion of the Japanese Government as set
                    forth in the last paragraph of your 135, August 9, 1 p.m. Presumably it will be
                    embodied in the formal reply of the Japanese Government whereupon the Department
                    will be prepared to submit it to the other Powers concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
